      • splitAllowEmpty

        public static final java.util.List<java.lang.String> splitAllowEmpty(java.lang.String source,
                                                                     java.lang.String sep,
                                                                     java.lang.String remove)
        Splitting the specified string (source string) into a list of words (tokens). The character (string) that is used for separation is specified by the parameter sep. The returned list can be empty. For each returned word (token), the string that specified by the parameter remove is removed from such word.
        Parameters:
        source - specified string to be split.
        sep - character (string) that is used for separation.
        remove - the string which is removed from each tokens.
        Returns:
        List of words (tokens) from splitting the specified string. This list can be empty.
